title: WORKSHOP | Yes, you can host a house party!
description:
**Why host a house party?**  Yes, door knocks, phone banks, postcards, rallies are all important organizing tools.  But in 2025-26, we need to do something more and different to win.  House parties can:

- Reach voters outside of our political bubbles

- Have friend and neighbor conversations with those who support our democratic values

- Inoculate voters against the onslaught of right-wing media

- Expand our volunteer base

**Are you thinking about hosting a house party, but don't know how to get started?**  If you've never hosted one before (and even if you're a fellow introvert), or just want a refresher, join the Bay Area Coalition every Monday, 5 pm (PT) / 7 pm (CT) / 8 pm (ET) for our ** *nationwide* ** house party workshop ...

 - How to plan your house party

 - Tips and tools for hosting conversations with your friends, neighbors, colleagues

*You'll leave the workshop fired up and ready to host your house party!*

Sign up here for ** *California* ** house party workshops - https://www.mobilize.us/cadems/event/759747/

For more Bay Area Coalition actions: https://bayareacoalition.org/

title: March for a Car Free Silver Lake Park

address_lines: Silver Lake Park Road & Forest Avenue

description:
Silver Lake Park was envisioned as the Central Park of Staten Island’s North Shore. Home to dozens of wildlife species, including a family of nesting bald eagles, a weekly fun run, and a well used road for running, biking, playing, roller skating, and track practices, it’s been an oasis of open space since it was closed to vehicle traffic in 2020.  A haphazard move backed by Councilwoman Hanks, District Attorney McMahon, and Borough President Fossella to reintroduce vehicle traffic to the park is putting lives at risk. 

If you agree that parks are no place for cars, join Transportation Alternatives on May 10th for a march on the offices of Councilwoman Hanks and District Attorney McMahon! 

We will meet at the intersection of Silver Lake Park Road and Forest Avenue before a 1.7-mile march downhill to the offices of Councilwoman Hanks and District Attorney McMahon at 130 Stuyvesant Ave.

title: Indiana Fayette County Mens Club Meeting
description:
Embrace the Warmth and Support of Our Meetings and Breakfast Events
In the hustle and bustle of daily life, finding a place where one feels welcomed and supported can be a beacon of hope. Our community gatherings, whether meetings or breakfast events, provide just that—a warm embrace and a sense of belonging. These occasions are more than just gatherings; they are an opportunity to connect, share, and support each other, creating bonds that last a lifetime. If you want to feel like you've been part of a community for years, come and visit us.
Feel Like You Belong
One of the most remarkable aspects of our meetings and breakfast events is the immediate sense of belonging they offer. From the moment you walk in, you will be greeted with open arms and friendly smiles. Our members are passionate about welcoming newcomers and making them feel like part of the family. This inclusivity is not just about making you feel comfortable; it is about genuinely integrating you into the fabric of our community.
Regular Meetings
Our meetings are held regularly and serve as a platform for members to share their thoughts, ideas, and experiences. These meetings are structured yet informal, allowing for open dialogue and spontaneous interactions. Whether you have been attending for years or are joining for the first time, you will find that your voice is valued and your contributions are appreciated.

•	Topics: Wide-ranging discussions from personal growth to community projects.
•	Format: Interactive sessions with plenty of opportunities for everyone to participate.

Our breakfast events are another cornerstone of our community spirit. These gatherings are not only about enjoying a delicious meal together but also about fostering deeper connections. Sharing a meal is a timeless tradition that brings people closer, and our breakfast events are designed to do just that.
•	Atmosphere: Casual and relaxed, perfect for bonding over breakfast.
•	Menu: A variety of options to cater to all dietary preferences.
•	Activities: Lighthearted activities that encourage interaction and laughter.
Supporting Each Other
A core principle of our community is mutual support. We believe in lifting each other up and being there through thick and thin. Our meetings and breakfast events are a testament to this commitment. Members come together to share their challenges, successes, and aspirations, offering support and encouragement every step of the way.
Community Projects
Our gatherings often lead to the conception and execution of community projects. These projects are aimed at improving the lives of our members and the broader community. Whether it’s a local cleanup, a charity drive, or an educational workshop, our members collaborate to make a positive impact.
•	Initiatives: Member-driven projects that address local needs.
•	Participation: Everyone is encouraged to contribute their skills and time.
•	Impact: Tangible benefits for the community and personal fulfillment for participants.
Personal Growth
Supporting each other also means fostering personal growth. Our meetings and breakfast events provide an environment where members can learn, grow, and develop new skills. Through shared experiences and collective wisdom, members find opportunities for personal advancement and self-improvement.
•	Learning: Workshops and discussions that promote learning and development.
•	Mentoring: Experienced members offer guidance and support to newcomers.
•	Goals: Setting and achieving personal and community goals together.
Building Lasting Connections
The friendships and connections formed at our meetings and breakfast events are enduring and meaningful. These bonds go beyond the gatherings themselves, extending into daily life and creating a network of support that members can rely on.
Networking Opportunities
Our gatherings provide excellent networking opportunities. Members come from diverse backgrounds and professions, offering a wealth of knowledge and experience. This diversity enriches our discussions and projects, leading to innovative solutions and collaborations.
•	Professional Connections: Build relationships that can advance your career and personal projects.
•	Social Connections: Form friendships that enhance your social life and well-being.
•	Collaborations: Opportunities to work together on community and personal initiatives.
A Lifelong Community
Joining our community means becoming part of something bigger—an extended family that supports you through all stages of life. Whether you’re facing a difficult challenge or celebrating a milestone, our members are there to share in your journey.
•	Consistency: Regular gatherings ensure ongoing support and engagement.
•	Accessibility: Events are designed to be inclusive and accessible to all members.
•	Commitment: A shared commitment to each other and to the community’s well-being.
In conclusion, we invite you to visit us at any of our meetings or breakfast events. Experience the joy of being part of a community that values inclusivity, support, and lasting connections. Join us, and you will feel you have been a cherished member for years. Together, we can achieve great things and create a positive impact on each other and our community.
